I have been coming to V Spot for 5 years for one item that I think they make better than anyone else: their vegan BLAT. When I lived abroad, this was the item I missed from home. Today, I discovered that they changed the recipe. Without warning. It is now made with one piece of the tempeh (as opposed to the handful they provided previously), and deep fried onion rings (which incidentally I happen to loath). It also no longer comes with a side. The price, has not changed accordingly. When I called to ask about it, they said they had no intention to change the recipe back to the original, and I would have to call grubhub for any kind of compensation. Even though the mistake was neither theirs nor mine. I understand that restaurants are struggling now, but if they're going to change the recipe, they should provide some clue to that effect. And when a loyal customer says something, the onus should not be on them to try to recoup the associated funds.

This was my first visit to the Brooklyn location. It's always nice to find a vegan healthy restaurant with food that taste good & actually like the real (dairy) alternative. Got to the restaurant just before the happy hour ended & ordered a margarita. The drink was just ok. I did appreciate that it was not sweet but it was missing flavor. Now on to the main event.....Nachos & Quesadillas. Nachos were very fresh. I would love it if the tortillas chips were baked instead of fried. The vegan cheese & beans, salsa & guacamole were all great. The quesadillas were equally great. Looks like the use Ezekiel type tortillas & it definitely feels  like you're eating healthier. The filling was good & i liked that the plantains inside didn't make it taste sweet. I would like the food to have a little kick....maybe option of fresh jalapenos would be nice. For dessert it was the Brownie Sundae. I was not so impressed but my son devourered it. What kid doesn't like sugar? That's why I am writing this review...lol. For me the brownie was too gooey & I've had much better vegan ice cream. I find the not so good vegan versions of desserts always contain too much sugar. This wasn't the case here but flavor & texture were missing. Overall it was good food experience & I recommend dining here for a good vegan meal.

-Flavorless Food -Spicy Customer Service  I went here to celebrate my Anniversary with my boyfriend. The server was rude and very dry. The food needed to be seasoned. It had no depth of flavor, well no flavor at all. It didn't taste like they used any salt or pepper. The empanadas I had were Philly cheese steak and the Jamaican. The Philly cheese steak taste like nothing, the Jamaican only tasted spicy but it had no specific flavor profile. Once we finished the appetizer the server brought out the entree yet left the dirty appetizer plate on the table. She never asked if we were ok, or if we needed anything. I made a mistake with the drink order. She scolded me for my mistake. I waited about 25 mins for her to bring my new drink. She apologized for the wait but it seemed forced, not sincere. The kale ceasar had about 10% kale and 90 % romaine. The ceasar salad dressing tasted like nothing. The salad came with huge red onions on top that would be very awkward to try to eat on a date. The tempeh saved the salad because it was salty therefore it gave it flavor. My boyfriends sandwich tasted like nothing and it was dry! They had housemade salsa on the table. I put it on my food to spice it up a bit and I couldn't believe the salsa also tasted like nothing! The nachos and buffalo wings were good. Everything else needed at bare minimum SALT AND PEPPER! I was really looking forward to eating here and I was very disappointed in the food and even more in the service. If you want food that taste like water I would recommend going here.

Consistently awful customer service. Long time customer will not be back. I am vegan and have been going here for years. Different staff over the years and down the line are just awful save maybe one or two waitresses/managers who are no longer there. Over half the time they screw up the order whether it is the wrong item altogether or a missing ingredient. The last time I went they gave me a chicken cutlet sandwich instead of chicken parm sandwich. This happens ALL THE TIME. 2 similar sounding items on the menu, sure but you would think if they work there, they know the difference. Sent it back. Portabella salad next and it was missing the pecans and the cashew cheese. The waiter tried to tell me those are extra items you have to request. No they are not. I showed him the menu. Instead of arguing with the customer, try apologizing! When I asked him, what do you expect me to do, pay full price for something missing 2 ingredients? He said well we can make you a new one or you can go somewhere else. I left and won't be back. Mind you, I am someone who has gone there for years dropping anywhere from 50-100 dollars a month in this place. I have put up with the consistently bad service because I do like their food and want to support 100% vegan places but enough is enough. A new vegan place opened down the block from them. Traditional Latin cuisine served in the trendy Park Slope area of Brooklyn, NY providing customers with an exclusively vegan menu but lackluster quality and presentation.  Food *** The homemade tortilla chips are very good and one the more unique we’ve had. However, the salsa they provide is in a very small holder for it (and very small amount), making it difficult to apply the salsa to the chips. We got the Chipotle burrito and the VSPOT burrito. The VSPOT burrito came to the table lukewarm, while the Chipotle burrito was heated properly as observed by the steam that came out when opened. I enjoyed my Chipotle burrito but my partner was not a fan of the VSPOT.  Atmosphere **** Lively, popular, and intimate all at the same time. They definitely did well here. The only thing keeping it from five stars is the square footage of the space and there could be some improvements to the interior.  Service *** Overall not bad, but the waiters switched in the midst of our dining experience and we were not informed. However, food was served at a reasonable time and a bottle of water provided to the table (definitely a star in itself)!  Price $$ Reasonably priced food.  We won’t give up on VSPOT and will probably check it out for brunch since we’ve read that their brunches are pretty amazing!

Went here for brunch and it was wonderful. The faux meat is getting to the point where it's indistinguishable from real meat. I had the "New York City breakfast" which came with "sausage".
